org.conqat.lib.commons.cache4j

Class ThreadLocalCache<K,V,X extends java.lang.Exception>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.commons.cache4j.ThreadLocalCache<K,V,X>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type. This must have both Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode() correctly implemented.
    V - the value type. It is generally recommended to use an immutable type here, but this is not required.
    X - the type of exception thrown. If no exception will be throws, use NeverThrownRuntimeException.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICache<K,V,X>

    public class ThreadLocalCache<K,V,X extends java.lang.Exception>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ICache<K,V,X>
    Implementation of a cache that manages a separate backend for each thread, thus isolating threads from each other. Note that accessing this cache from many temporary threads can lead to memory leaks (as the cached data is still stored) for certain backends.
